  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense under the legislation of most countries. It is typically addressed in criminal codes or specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws. Money laundering involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money, usually by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. Many countries have strict laws and penalties for money laundering, including:\n\n1. Substantial fines\n2. Imprisonment\n3. Asset seizure\n4. Criminal prosecution\n\nThe specific legal provisions and penalties can vary between jurisdictions, but money laundering is generally considered a serious financial crime.",
